      "id": "b7cb0ed8f892d503",
      "text": "In order to move forward, we propose an abstracting conceptualization. We replace the concept of action as the ultimate concept with the concept of observation. An observation always exists when a distinction is made in order to designate one (but not the other) side of the distinction."
