        "id": "b0058a6046ec4c5b",
        "text": "Above all, however, the relationship between the decision and the alternative needs to be clarified. The alternative does not decide itself. Not even dialectical theories, which were based on \"opposites\", would have claimed that the opposites cancel themselves out. A further factor was needed – called concept or spirit or revolution. But if a decision (or even a decision-maker capable of acting) is needed in order to choose one of the alternatively connected possibilities: what is this decision, who is this decision-maker?"
      },
      "date": 1706619717952
